In [[North America]]n [[slang]], a '''big ticket item''' is an end luxury item. Although usually referring to an item of significant physical size (e.g. a [[computer]], [[sports car]] or big screen [[television]]), the term can be applied to almost any expensive item. The term is derived from the idea that the price is high ("big") and that larger products have physically larger price tags ("big ticket").

Some items are constant big ticket items, such as [[jewelry]] and [[state-of-the-art]] televisions, while others may fall out of the category after an initial rush at introduction. 

